1 This program of instruction shall be provided to each public school for use in its
2 course of instruction. The program of instruction, at a minimum, shall include the
3 provisions of 4 U.S.C. secs. 1 to 3 and[ 4 U.S.C. secs.] 5 to 9.
4 (4) The board of education of each local school district may purchase or otherwise
5 acquire and provide for display in each classroom copies of the Declaration of
6 Independence, the Gettysburg Address, and other documents the local board deems
7 significant to the history of Kentucky and the United States.[
8 (5) (a) The board of education of each local school district shall establish a policy
9 and develop procedures whereby, at the commencement of the first class of
10 each day in all public schools, there shall be a moment of silence or reflection
11 of at least one (1) minute, but not to exceed two (2) minutes, in duration.
12 (b) The policy required in paragraph (a) of this subsection shall ensure that all
13 pupils remain seated and silent and make no distracting display so that each
14 pupil may, in the exercise of his or her individual choice, meditate, pray, or
15 engage in any other silent activity which does not interfere with, distract from,
16 or impede other pupils' exercise of individual choice. The policy shall prohibit
17 district personnel from providing instruction to any student regarding the
18 nature of any reflection that a student may engage in during the moment of
19 silence or reflection. The policy shall require notification be sent to parents or
20 guardians providing information on the policy and encouraging parents and
21 guardians to provide guidance to their pupils regarding the moment of silence
22 or reflection.]
